<p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
   xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
   n="2"
   xml:lang="ar-Arab"
   style="direction:rtl; unicode-bidi:embed"
   part="N">جودر حكيم فاضل من حكماء ا<placeName ref="https://usaybia.net/place/260"
              resp="#mtolay"
              instant="false"
              full="yes">لهند</placeName> وعلمائه متميز في أيامه وله نظر في الطب وتصانيف في العلوم الحكمية وله من الكتب: كتاب المواليد وهو قد نقل إلى العربي.‬‎</p>
<p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
   xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
   n="2"
   xml:lang="en-Latn"
   part="N">
                            A distinguished figure among the scholars and learned men of India, who was highly regarded by his contemporaries, particularly as an authority on medicine. Jawdar is the author of scholarly works on various subjects, including
                            <hi rend="italic">On Nativities</hi>
                            (
                            <hi rend="italic">K. al-mawālīd</hi>
                            ), which has been translated into Arabic.
                        </p>
